  "prompt": "What are the best coffee shops with Wi-Fi in San Francisco for evening work?",
  "response": "San Francisco has a vibrant caf\u00e9 culture, and many coffee shops provide a great atmosphere for evening work with Wi-Fi. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Blue Bottle Coffee** - Known for its quality brews, Blue Bottle locations typically offer a calm environment perfect for working. The locations in the Mission and on Mint Street are particularly conducive to evening work.\n\n2. **Philz Coffee** - With multiple locations throughout the city, Philz is famous for its personalized coffee blends. Some locations have ample seating and a relaxed vibe, making them suitable for working in the evening.\n\n3. **Ritual Coffee Roasters** - This chain is well-loved for its high-quality coffee and has a few locations that can be great for working. The caf\u00e9 in the Mission District is spacious and often not too crowded in the evenings.\n\n4. **The Mill** - Located on Divisadero Street, The Mill offers a great atmosphere for working. They have a spacious seating area and a selection of artisanal toast alongside their coffee.\n\n5. **Caf\u00e9 R\u00e9veille** - With a modern, inviting atmosphere, Caf\u00e9 R\u00e9veille in the Mission District is a great spot to work in the evening. They offer good coffee and a relaxed vibe.\n\n6. **Sightglass Coffee** - The SoMa location is spacious and has a great ambiance for working. They serve excellent coffee and often have plenty of seating available.\n\n7. **Stumptown Coffee Roasters** - The location on Guerrero Street provides a cozy environment with good coffee, making it a nice spot for evening work.\n\n8. **Tandem Coffee** - Although a bit smaller, Tandem Coffee has a welcoming atmosphere and good Wi-Fi, making it suitable for focused work.\n\n9. **Sey Coffee** - Located in the Mission, Sey Coffee offers a calm environment and high-quality coffee, ideal for evening work sessions.\n\n10. **Peet's Coffee** - Various Peet's locations around the city are reliable choices for working, with plenty of seating and a casual atmosphere.\n\nBe sure to check the specific location's hours, as some may close earlier than others. Also, consider visiting during off-peak hours to find a quieter space for work.",
